      • calculateNijk

        public int calculateNijk(Node node,
                         int parentConfig,
                         int valueK)
        Function that calculates Nijk for a given node, parentConfig and value This function runs all the parent's values, to find the wanted values. Then, it saves a TreeSet with the respective indexes of those values, and uses the retain function with the other parents Tree. It proceeds to calculate the number of values wanted in the childNode that correspond to the indexes contained in the father's TreeSet
        Parameters:
        node - node to which is intended to calculte Nijk
        parentConfig - father configuration to be used
        valueK - value of the wanted feature
        Returns:
        int with the node's Nijk

      • isDag

        public boolean isDag()
        Method with an algorithm that tests if a network is acyclic Creats two LinkedLists, one with all visited nodes, and one with unvisited nodes, being the latter a copy of the original nodeList. The function visitNode complements this method
        Returns:
        boolean true if dag, false otherwise

      • argMax

        public DynamicBayesNetwork argMax()
        Function that manipulates the network, using the add, flip and remove steps. This function tries each step and compares the obtained score to the previous steps( of the same kind. i.e. if a better add is found, it is saved over the last add). If better, the step is saved and built in to the new DynamicBayesNetwork
        Returns:
        DynamicBayesNetwork Network with best score
